You can leave the house at five o'clock in the morning and run to the hospital to be the first, but you are not the first.
There are many patients.
Some people die because they have to wait.
The situation has hardly changed since Bwell father died in 2002.
In Cameroon, there is only one doctor for 5,000 people, according to the World Health Organisation.
In the United States, however, the ratio is a doctor for 413 people.
